4
00:01:43,180 --> 00:01:48,100
My private warehouse is guarded in three shifts day and night.

5
00:01:48,100 --> 00:01:51,719
How could mere water bandits possibly sneak in and steal things?

6
00:01:51,719 --> 00:01:56,859
Moreover, no one has reported any thefts previously.

7
00:01:56,859 --> 00:02:01,100
It must be those water bandits spouting nonsense.

8
00:02:01,100 --> 00:02:04,780
They said this fire oil was rare and hard to come by.

9
00:02:04,780 --> 00:02:08,080
They secretly hid a jar before committing arson.

10
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:12,839
Let's bring them up in a moment. Compare the two oils, and it'll become clear.

11
00:02:17,140 --> 00:02:21,580
Why would these water bandits burn your garden for no reason?

12
00:02:21,580 --> 00:02:25,300
They were hired by someone, paid to do the job.

13
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:29,779
Who has the audacity to harm my Floral Envoy?!

14
00:02:29,779 --> 00:02:34,490
Your Majesty, the water bandits confessed that it was

15
00:02:35,260 --> 00:02:37,510
County Princess Ji An.

16
00:02:49,499 --> 00:02:54,800
Your Majesty, I've never met this person. This is slander.

17
00:02:55,339 --> 00:02:59,580
You Zhen is a lady of the inner chambers. What would she know about fire oil?

18
00:02:59,580 --> 00:03:02,780
There must be some misunderstanding.

19
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:08,020
If the County Princess says no, I certainly believe it.

20
00:03:08,979 --> 00:03:11,580
What truth could possibly come from the mouths of water bandits?

21
00:03:11,580 --> 00:03:16,160
They probably stole the fire oil and wanted to frame the County Princess.

22
00:03:16,900 --> 00:03:22,239
However, the oil has burned down to just 50 barrels. There's no further evidence.

23
00:03:22,239 --> 00:03:26,059
We don't know how much they actually stole at the beginning.

24
00:03:26,059 --> 00:03:31,859
What if they hid more than one jar? What if they have other accomplices?

25
00:03:31,859 --> 00:03:35,059
Wouldn't that mean Chang'an is in grave danger?

26
00:03:39,099 --> 00:03:43,700
Jingzhao Prefecture stop overseeing this matter. Leave it to Ministry of Justice.

27
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:47,019
On what date was the fire oil confiscated? How long did it remain in the treasury?

28
00:03:47,019 --> 00:03:50,200
Through whose hands did it pass? Do the water bandits have accomplices?

29
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:52,460
Have they hidden any other dangerous items?

30
00:03:52,460 --> 00:03:56,260
You must investigate all this thoroughly.

31
00:03:56,260 --> 00:03:58,379
Yes, Your Majesty.

32
00:04:04,539 --> 00:04:08,339
No need to investigate further. I'm the one who did it.

33
00:04:10,420 --> 00:04:14,420
Your Majesty, I was dissatisfied because my husband cared for his ex-wife.

34
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:18,339
This drove me to irrationality and I sought revenge.

35
00:04:18,339 --> 00:04:23,140
I stole fire oil from my father's treasury and had Fragrance Garden set on fire.

36
00:04:23,140 --> 00:04:27,060
You Zhen, you're so muddled!

37
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:31,099
This now involves the Ministry of Justice.

38
00:04:31,099 --> 00:04:37,299
I don't wish my mistake to tarnish my father's reputation, bringing him trouble.

39
00:04:37,299 --> 00:04:40,739
I'm terrified and full of regret.

40
00:04:40,739 --> 00:04:42,820
I beg Your Majesty for forgiveness.

41
00:04:45,339 --> 00:04:51,480
Previously, Liu Chang searched my store, and now you set fire to my garden.

42
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:53,979
You two are taking turns targeting me.

43
00:04:53,979 --> 00:04:59,339
Is it because you're jealous Mu Dan and I are in love and wealth is pouring in for us?

44
00:05:01,260 --> 00:05:03,400
Your Highness, you must stand up for me.

45
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:08,020
Otherwise, I'll never dare to set foot in your mansion again.

46
00:05:12,219 --> 00:05:18,380
Rest assured, Sui Zhi. I'll give you a proper explanation.

47
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:25,539
A prince who commits a crime is subject to the same punishment as a commoner.

48
00:05:25,539 --> 00:05:28,390
This is You Zhen's fault.

49
00:05:28,390 --> 00:05:32,380
Without punishment, it won't appease the public's anger.

50
00:05:32,380 --> 00:05:36,399
Official Ren handle this according to the law.

51
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:42,579
For intentional arson, it warrants...

52
00:05:42,579 --> 00:05:47,299
three years of penal servitude and exile of 2,000 li.

53
00:05:47,299 --> 00:05:49,199
Okay.

54
00:05:50,639 --> 00:05:55,260
However, considering her voluntary confession,

55
00:05:55,260 --> 00:05:58,060
the punishment can be reduced.

56
00:05:58,670 --> 00:06:00,650
Why not...

57
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:08,060
Why not impose a light punishment as a warning? Your Majesty, what do you think?

58
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:23,179
Your righteous stand against personal ties truly sets an example for all ministers.

59
00:06:23,179 --> 00:06:27,339
No matter what, You Zhen is my niece.

60
00:06:27,339 --> 00:06:30,539
Receiving punishment in public would be disgraceful to the royal family's dignity.

61
00:06:30,539 --> 00:06:34,659
Just punish her privately in the palace and give the people an explanation.

62
00:06:34,659 --> 00:06:36,779
Yes, Your Majesty.

63
00:06:37,380 --> 00:06:43,620
The one who suffered from this is Sui Zhi. Does this handling of it satisfy you?

64
00:06:43,620 --> 00:06:47,380
Your Majesty is wise, I'm certainly satisfied.

65
00:06:47,380 --> 00:06:53,940
Public grievances are appeased, but funds for repairing the garden are still needed.

66
00:06:53,940 --> 00:07:01,260
I'll have the money for repairing Fragrance Garden sent to your residence tomorrow.

67
00:07:02,219 --> 00:07:04,380
Thank you, Your Highness.

68
00:07:28,239 --> 00:07:32,639
Your Highness, it's time.

